(thirdQuint)Study of Bendamustine and IXAZOMIB (MLN9708) Plus Dexamethasone in Relapsed/Refractory Multiple Myeloma.

 OVERVIEW: This Phase I/II study is designed to first identify doses of MLN9708 and bendamustine that are associated with an acceptable adverse event profile when delivered together in 28-day cycles.

 Additionally, the study aims to assess the efficacy of the combination in patients with relapsed/refractory multiple myeloma.

 Responders (stable disease or more),will continue to receive up to eight cycles total in the absence of further progressive disease.

